I think after you decrement the count, this is all you need to do here. Please correct me if you find this is not the case when re-testing.

if (!sensor.functional() && sensor.getCounter() == 0)
{
    updateState(sensor);
}

If the method is not `timebased` but the "allowed_out_of_range_time" config is given, it can simply be ignored...no error necessary really. Also, this seems it could be simplified to:

if (method == MethodMode::timebased)
{
    if (!fan.contains("allowed_out_of_range_time"))
    {
        // Log error on missing required parameter
        log<level::ERR>(
            "Missing required fan monitor definition parameters",
            entry("REQUIRED_PARAMETER=%s",
                  "{allowed_out_of_range_time}"));
            throw std::runtime_error(
                "Missing required fan monitor definition parameters");
    }
    else
    {
        timeout = fan["allowed_out_of_range_time"].get<size_t>();
    }
}
